commit.message: Converted BlobItem and BlobItemProperties to be wrappers around generated types

nodes.bodyText: nit : add a new line to the end in swagger README

Is this ok to do since BlobItemInternal is "private" and BlobItem is public. Would it be better to like extract the pieces in a private method wherever you use this constructor and make this constructor like take in all the properties?
Is there a clean way we could unduplicate this code? I'm not sure where it could live though.
Why are there 2 similar seeming constructors added? Is it to make the OR logic separate from the max constructor?
Nice, I think this is a great way to test features that need to be configured a specific way
